Configuration Panel

This is used to set up the individual timeouts/delays/transition time for the individual SEAT COMPONENTS like: seat base, back rest etc.


MQTT messages: 
    audi_seat/seat_motion/lateral:front # move seat base →
    audi_seat/seat_motion/lateral:back  # move seat base ←
    audi_seat/seat_motion/lateral:stop  # stop lateral motion
    
    audi_seat/seat_motion/vertical:up   # move seat base ↑
    audi_seat/seat_motion/vertical:down # move seat base ↓
    audi_seat/seat_motion/vertical:stop # stop vertical motion
    
    audi_seat/back_rest_motion:front # move seat base →
    audi_seat/back_rest_motion:back  # move seat base ←
    audi_seat/back_rest_motion:stop  # stop lateral motion
    
    audi_seat/massage: start         # starts massage
    audi_seat/massage: stop          # stops masssage
The forward, backward, up, down and other functions are sent by the marked buttons. Upon sending the commands, It starts counting the time elapsed.
Pressing the consequitive STOP buttons:
  1. Sends respective Stop commands via MQTT
  2. Stores the respective durations, up until that time, in DB.

Those durations are used in setting limits for each motion, as in:

If I ask the SEAT BASE only to move FORWARD, then my system will send: 
     audi_seat/seat_motion/lateral:front # seat base →
     
     delay [ duration saved for seat base's forward motion ]
     
     audi_seat/seat_motion/lateral:stop  # seat base stops
This way we can create complex choreographies of motion from our main control panel. The main control module will send signals here and we keep this module running but only use it for set up in the beginiing phases]
